column1: During this COVID-19 pandemic access to affordable quality health coverage is more important than ever. Enrollment in https://t.co/xHOxNkoNur is open from November 1 to December 15.  Coverage may be more affordable than you think. #GetCovered

The #COVID19 crisis has put a spotlight on what we've known for decades: our nation has failed to prioritize the needs of working mothers. We need real solutions for the 'she-session' brought from the pandemic like the ones the House passed in the #HEROESAct #momsbailout

The #COVID19 pandemic is FUELING the housing crisis. Millions of Americans are facing EVICTION.  #KnowYour Rights. Find out if you qualify for protection from eviction.   Visit https://t.co/sR33dL1sPm for more information. https://t.co/XkRs7NxEI9
Thinking of the President and First Lady as they both have tested positive for COVID19.  This virus should be taken very seriously - wishing them a full and speedy recovery.

We’re facing two crises at once -- the COVID-19 pandemic and an addiction epidemic that is claiming thousands of lives each year. This #RecoveryMonth I’m wearing purple to show those who are struggling that recovery is possible. https://t.co/jRAcTy8ld3

Women make up 52% of essential workers during the #COVID19 pandemic. And Women of Color - including Latinas - are the most likely to work in low-wage jobs where they are being shortchanged by a combined gender and racial wage gap. https://t.co/XW77sz6qgu

Looking forward to discussing with you law enforcement reform 2020 Census response and COVID19 safety today August 4th at 7:30PM during my telephone town hall  - details attached! https://t.co/DHoCAQggrL

#COVID19 has had devastating health & economic impacts on women & families—especially women of color with Black & Latina women facing unemployment rates of 14.1% & 15.4%. @HouseDemocrats passed the #HeroesAct MONTHS ago to ease this burden. @SenateGOP must #PassTheHeroesAct! https://t.co/7kz9fSbjDW
ALL are essential workers on the front lines of the #COVID19 pandemic. We must ensure they all have access to quality affordable health care. Their health is our health. https://t.co/tgH3WPZLFB

The decision by @ICEgov requiring international students to leave the U.S. if their institutions opt for on-line only classes due to #Covid19 is a serious blow to the U.S. economy and hinders retention of diverse talent that keeps this Nation in the forefront of innovation.
#COVID19 has caused devastating health and economic impacts for women and their families especially women of color. The people need action. Senate GOP must pass the #HeroesAct NOW! #FamiliesFirst

.As we face the #Covid19 pandemic we are reminded of just how critical workers are to our supply chain infrastructure. Thank you #ToThoseWhoKeepUsMoving for all of your hard work during this unprecedented crisis. https://t.co/dQZdMg59Tt

#Smallbiz are facing problems with SBA #COVID19 programs. @senatemajldr’s bill doesn’t address them. @housedemocrats are working to fix these problems by: -Providing more $ for disaster grants and loans -Empowering local lenders to get #PPP money to vulnerable communities. https://t.co/hU8s4U5NaT

This year #BlackMaternalHealthWeek comes in the midst of a pandemic. The racial disparities in COVID-19 outcomes reflect ongoing disparities in maternal mortality rates in the US. As a Member of the @BMHCaucus I am working hard to address this crisis. #BMHW20 https://t.co/Tl6eMdVsvI

Today I along with 92 Members sent a letter calling for significant funds for homelessness in CARES 2. Thanks @RepHastingsFL for your partnership! No one should face homelessness or housing insecurity during #COVID19. https://t.co/KTrH7b3kn4

Today for National Minority Health Month I led a resolution w/@RepLouCorrea and 91 Members demanding action on the disproportionate impact of #COVID19 on communities of color. Our families deserve better care and better outcomes than what they are enduring now. #NMHM2020

Today I along w/53 Members sent a letter to the White House Coronavirus Taskforce to ensure  medication access for #lupus and rheumatoid arthritis patients during #COVID19. Thanks @RepMcKinley@USRepKeating @RepPeteKing & @RepDebDingell for partnering on this effort! https://t.co/XnyN3jfPPq
